<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1059,1093,1654]" box="[136,377,1093,1117]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">DISTRIBUTION (Fig. 3)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1059,1093,1654]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[212,341,1125,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orni">
<emphasis box="[212,341,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Cicada orni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most popular European cicada due to its remarkable chorus song and its wide distribution area. If Swiss non-scientists speak about cicadas they normally refer to this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1059,1093,1654]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">
<bibRefCitation author="FUESSLIN, J. C." box="[212,383,1221,1245]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" refId="ref16256" refString="FUESSLIN, J. C. 1775. Verzeichnis der ihm bekannten Schweitzerischen Inseckten. Bey dem Verfasser und in Commission bey Heinrich Steiner und Compagnie, Zurich und Winterthur, XII + 62 pp." type="book" year="1775">Fuesslin (1775)</bibRefCitation>
knew 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[462,541,1222,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orni">
<emphasis box="[462,541,1222,1245]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">C. orni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Valais as “very abundant”. 
<bibRefCitation author="SAUSSURE, H. - B. DE" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" refId="ref18815" refString="SAUSSURE, H. - B. DE 1780. Voyages dans les Alpes, precedes d'un Essai sur l'Histoire Naturelle des Environs de Geneve. Samuel Fauche, Imprimeur &amp; Librairedu Roi, Neuchatel, Tome Premier, 540 pp." type="book" year="1780">Saussure (1780)</bibRefCitation>
wrote that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[338,416,1253,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orni">
<emphasis box="[338,416,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">C. orni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is completely missing in the Geneva region and provides herewith an interesting absence record in very old literature. Labram &amp;Imhoff(1845) reported it from the most southern parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[598,725,1315,1339]" name="Switzerland" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
where it was locally abundant. 
<bibRefCitation author="CURTI, G." box="[136,268,1347,1371]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" refId="ref15760" refString="CURTI, G. 1846. Storia naturale disposta con ordine scientifico eadattata alla comune intelligenza. Tipografia Meyer, Lucerna, 528 pp." type="book" year="1846">Curti (1846)</bibRefCitation>
thought 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[362,436,1348,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orni">
<emphasis box="[362,436,1348,1371]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">C. orni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be restricted to 
<collectingRegion box="[633,704,1347,1371]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Ticino</collectingRegion>
, some parts of 
<collectingRegion box="[863,946,1347,1371]" country="Switzerland" name="Graubuenden" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Grisons</collectingRegion>
and found occasionally in the 
<collectingRegion box="[341,410,1378,1402]" country="Switzerland" name="Valais" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Valais</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="SEILER, A." box="[419,559,1378,1402]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" pagination="160 - 175" refId="ref19120" refString="SEILER, A. 1847. Uebersicht der im Canton Schaffhausen vorkommenden Thiere. V erhandlungen der Schweizerischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft 32: 160 - 175." type="journal article" year="1847">Seiler (1847)</bibRefCitation>
listed the species as uncommon for the 
<collectingRegion country="Switzerland" name="Schaffhausen" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Canton of Schaffhausen</collectingRegion>
, but we doubt its validity since he does not report 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1772" box="[854,1058,1410,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[854,1058,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Cicadetta montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[136,172,1441,1465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<bibRefCitation author="HAGEN, H." box="[179,337,1441,1466]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" pagination="27 - 37" refId="ref16722" refString="HAGEN, H. 1856 a. Die Sing-Cicaden Europa's. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 17: 27 - 37." type="journal article" year="1856">Hagen (1856a)</bibRefCitation>
cites Bremi who has found it as the most common species in 
<collectingRegion box="[983,1055,1441,1465]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Ticino</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="TSCHUDI, F. VON" box="[136,299,1473,1497]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" refId="ref19737" refString="TSCHUDI, F. VON 1872. Das Thierleben der Alpenwelt. Naturansichten und Thierzeichnungen aus dem schweizerischen Gebirge. Verlagsbuchhandlung J. J. Weber, Leipzig, neunte, vielfach vermehrte und verbesserte Auflage, XV + 593 pp." type="book" year="1872">Tschudi (1872)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[371,499,1473,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orni">
<emphasis box="[371,499,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Cicada orni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as abundant in both 
<collectingRegion box="[723,792,1473,1497]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Ticino</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[844,909,1473,1497]" country="Switzerland" name="Valais" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Valais</collectingRegion>
with arecord altitude of “ 
<quantity box="[262,366,1504,1528]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15824" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" unit="ft" value="3800.0">3800 feet</quantity>
” (≈ 1150 ma.s.l.) for the upper 
<collectingRegion box="[703,772,1504,1528]" country="Switzerland" name="Valais" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Valais</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="ROUGEMONT, P. DE" box="[782,978,1504,1529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" pagination="29 - 38" refId="ref18788" refString="ROUGEMONT, P. DE 1880. Note sur l'helicopsyche sperata. Bulletin de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles de Neuchatel 12: 29 - 38." type="journal article" year="1880">Rougemont (1880</bibRefCitation>
, p. 33) mentioned “un charivari vraiment méridional” at Fully (VS) (= atrue Mediterranean pandemonium). 
<bibRefCitation author="BUGNION, E." box="[311,481,1567,1591]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" refId="ref15673" refString="BUGNION, E. 1890. Introduction ala faune entomologique du Valais (pp. IX-XLIV). In: F AVRE, E. Faune des Coleopteres du Valais et des regions limitrophes. Neue Denkschriften der allgemeinen schweizerischen Gesellschaft fur die gesamten Naturwissenschaften, Druck Zurcher und Furrer, Zurich, Band 31, XLIV + 448 pp." type="book" year="1890">Bugnion (1890)</bibRefCitation>
described the species as very common from Martigny (VS) to Sierre (VS), but missing at Montreux (VD) and Lausanne (VD). 
<bibRefCitation author="STOLL, O." box="[929,1058,1598,1622]" pageId="8" pageNumber="237" pagination="145 - 208" refId="ref19299" refString="STOLL, O. 1901. Uber xerotherme Relikte in der Schweizer Fauna der Wirbellosen. Jahresberichte der Geographisch-Ethnographischen Gesellschaft in Zurich 2: 145 - 208." type="journal article" year="1901">Stoll (1901)</bibRefCitation>
repeated the occurrence in the 
<collectingRegion box="[470,535,1630,1654]" country="Switzerland" name="Valais" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Valais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[590,659,1630,1654]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="8" pageNumber="237">Ticino</collectingRegion>
and added aremarkable observation
</paragraph>
